<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Moderate Earthquake Shakes Northern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- A moderate earthquake measuring
4.0 on the Richter scale shook the Northern Philippines tonight,
but no casualties or damage have been reported, the Philippine
Institute of Volcanology and Seismology said.
</P>
<P>
In a preliminary report, the institute said that the epicenter
was 58 kilometers southwest of Tagaytay City, Cavite Province.
</P>
<P>
The earthquake occurred at around 22:32 (14:32 GMT), the
institute said.
</P>
<P>
Seismologists say the Philippines is hit by an average of six
earthquakes every day but most of them are too weak to be felt.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
