<HEADLINE> Deng Xiaoping's Home Province Developing Rapidly (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 7 (Xinhua) -- At the ongoing "Glorious Five
Year Exhibition" in Beijing, a large photograph of late Chinese
leader Deng Xiaoping hangs over the entrance of the room reserved
for the accomplishments of Sichuan Province.
</P>
<P>
The material in the room is divided into four categories: the
new look of Sichuan Province; the glorious achievements of the
past five years; the great development of the whole society; and
Sichuan's bright future.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan covers an area of 485,000 sq km and has a population of
83.57 million. The 1996 gross domestic product in the southwest
province reached 298.5 billion yuan (36 billion US dollars),
accounting for 31.29 percent of the total GDP of the ten western
provinces and regions.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has placed much emphasis on the
construction of more highways and railways in the past five years,
and great achievements have been made to make the province more
accessible to other parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
The operation of the expressway between Chengdu and Chongqing
has initiated the construction of more high-grade expressways
across the province.
</P>
<P>
With the construction of the railways between Daxian and
Chengdu, Baoji and Chengdu, and the renovation of the railway
between Chengdu and Kunming, Sichuan is one of the regions in
China to have a high number of railways under construction at the
same time.
</P>
<P>
Shuangliu Airport at Chengdu has become the fourth-largest
international airport in China.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970908.0006 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dhaka Cancels Faulty GSP certificates under EU pressure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladeshi government today
decided to cancel irregular certificates whose holders enjoyed the
General System of Preference (GSP) facility in exporting garments
to the European market.
</P>
<P>
The decision was taken at a meeting today of the Cabinet
Committee on the GSP Problem headed by Finance Minister Shah AMS
Kibria, according to an official press release.
</P>
<P>
Earlier last month, the European Union (EU) threatened to
withdraw the GSP facility if Dhaka fails to cancel the inaccurate
GSP certificates by October 1.
</P>
<P>
The deadline was set by the EU after the Bangladeshi government
failed to take any measures to cancel 6,910 GSP certificates
which, an EU investigation team found late last year, were not
issued in compliance with the rules of origin.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh's garment industry, the country's biggest hard
currency earner, has been enjoying duty-free or low-duty treatment
under the GSP facility in the European market without any quota
restrictions.
</P>
<P>
However, the products must be made of indigenous materials to
get these privileges, which give the country's garment industry an
edge over its competitors.
</P>
<P>
Following complaints that the rules of origin clause are being
violated, the EU required Dhaka to cancel those alleged faulty
certificates. That would make the local exporters liable to pay
millions of U.S. dollars as an indirect compensation.
</P>
<P>
Official sources said the cabinet committee took the final
decision after heated debate on the issue.
</P>
<P>
The committee also said in the press release that it was the
government's firm policy to extend all possible help to promote
the country's export industries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970908.0007 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Comrade Deng Xiaoping's Home Province Developing Rapidly (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sichuan Province has a water energy resource reserve of 103
million kilowatts, accounting for one-fourth of the country's
total reserve.
</P>
<P>
The development of water energy resources has been the
province's investment and construction focus for the past five
years. The recently-completed Ertan hydropower station, which has
a capacity of 3.3 million kilowatts, is now the biggest hydropower
station ever built in China in this century.
</P>
<P>
The province has emerged as the country's third biggest grain
producer after breaking its harvest record four times. It has
also become the largest vegetable producer in west China.
</P>
<P>
The rapid development of Changhong Electronics Corporation,
Panzhihua Steel and Iron Corporation, and the China Oriental
Electric Corporation have greatly enhanced the province's
industrial strength, and given it a sharper market edge.
</P>
<P>
Also in the exhibit is an experimental magnetic suspension
train which has drawn the attention of most visitors. It was
donated to the show by Southwest Communications University in
Sichuan, and is the only such train designed exclusively by
Chinese scientists. China has become the third country in the
world to grasp this kind of high technology.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan Province has gathered the country's research force in
the field of space, aeronautics, nuclear power, electronics, and
biological technology. The Xichang satellite-launching base has
successfully sent a number of satellites into orbit in recent
years.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition also shows achievements in socialist ethical
 and cultural progress are also on display, the varied cultural
activities that have been held across the province, and some
outstanding artwork. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
