<HEADLINE> Romanian President Leaves for China Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Romanian President Emil
Constantinescu left here today for Beijing on a five-day state
visit to China.
</P>
<P>
He told Xinhua before his departure that during the visit he
will meet Chinese President Jiang Zemin, Premier Li Peng and other
Chinese leaders to discuss bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Romania "is willing to establish a lasting and mutual
beneficial partnership with China" and it is a part of Romania's
diplomatic strategy to develop relations with China and other
Asian countries, he said.
</P>
<P>
This will be Constantinescu's second visit to China. In 1989,
he visited China as the president of Bucharest University.
</P>
<P>
Accompanying the president in the visit are his wife, Nadia
Constantinescu, Foreign Minister Adrian Severin, aide to the
president's aide Dorin Marian, Cultural Minister Ion Caramitru and
20 Romanian business leaders.
</P>
<P>
Besides holding talks with Chinese businessmen, the Romanian
business leaders will meet officials from the Ministry of Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation, the Ministry of Coal and some
other ministries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
