<HEADLINE> PNA Criticizes Israel's Threats to Raid PNA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The Palestinian National
Authority (PNA) today strongly rejected Israel's threats to raid
the PNA territories in case of pursuing terrorists.
</P>
<P>
The Jerusalem Media and Communication Center (JMCC) quoted PNA
President Yasser Arafat's Information Advisor Nabil Abu Rodaineh
as saying in Gaza that "Palestinians will not accept such Israeli
practices and we have full rights to defend our lands, authority
and our religious sites."
</P>
<P>
Preparing for the unexpected raids by the Israeli military
forces, Palestinians are mobilized to set up road blocks at the
entrances of the cities, towns and villages of the West Bank and
Gaza Strip, JMCC said.
</P>
<P>
Following Thursday's bombings in Jerusalem's pedestrian mall
which killed seven people, the Israeli government criticized PNA
for failing to crack down on terrorism and threatened to raid the
PNA territories in case of pursuing terrorists.
</P>
<P>
Israeli forces reimposed the total closure on the West Bank and
Gaza Strip after Thursday's bombings which were carried out by
Hamas, or the Islamic Resistance Movement.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Prime minister Benjamin Netanyahu has ruled out any
peace negotiations with the Palestinians unless the PNA fights
against the terrorists. 
</P>
</TEXT>
