<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cape Verde PM Visits Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Carlos Veiga, Prime Minister
of Cape Verde arrived here today for an official visit, at the
invitation of his Angolan counterpart Franca Van-Dunem.
</P>
<P>
In a brief talk to the press today at the airport, Veiga said
the main aim for his visit is to promote friendship and mutually
supportive ties between the two peoples and governments.
</P>
<P>
He hopes that during his visit, the two sides will work
together to establish a firm partnership.
</P>
<P>
Reports had it that the two prime ministers will hold talks on
the present bilateral cooperation and problems involved. The two
sides will sign cooperation agreement in banking, visa exemption
of ordinary passport, the setting up of diplomatic institutions
and investment promotion and protection.
</P>
<P>
The two governments will also sign a protocol on Cape Verde's
providing 200 scholarships to Angola to train secondary and
advanced technical personnel.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, a trade agreement between Angola's
state-owned Petroleum Corporation and the energy provision
company of Cape Verde will also be signed.
</P>
<P>
This is Veiga's first visit to Angola. The visit was
originally set on Saturday, but had been put off due to technical
reasons.
</P>
<P>
Veiga will end his visit on September 11. 
</P>
</TEXT>
