<HEADLINE> Iran Declares Continuous Support for Palestinians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Parliament
Vice-Speaker Movahedi Kermani declared here today that Iran will
continue to support Palestinians in their struggle against
Israel.
</P>
<P>
Kermani said that the setback suffered by the Israelis in
southern Lebanon carried important messages for the Palestinian
nation, Arab states, the United States and the Israeli regime.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the open session of the Iranian Parliament, he
said that the defeat of the Israeli commandos in southern
Lebanon would one day lead to the total collapse of the Israeli
regime.
</P>
<P>
A special Israeli naval squad was ambushed by Hezbollah forces
early Friday morning near a village between Sidon and Tyre in
South Lebanon while on their way to carry out a raid mission.
</P>
<P>
Eleven commandos were killed, another soldier went missing,
presumed dead, and four others wounded in the fierce fighting.
</P>
<P>
Kermani said that the defeat had the message for the
Palestinian nation that they should further resist the Israelis.
</P>
<P>
He warned that those Arab countries, which are willing to
maintain their friendship with Israel, should know that they
would face strong reactions from their respective nations.
</P>
<P>
Kermani said the United States should know that the era of
bullying and hegemony is over and world peoples are now seeking
justice.
</P>
<P>
He made the statement only days before U.S. Secretary of
State Madeleine Albright is due to begin her first tour of the
Middle East Tuesday since she took office last January.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
