<HEADLINE> Hamas Spokesman Arrested in Amman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The Jordanian security authority
has arrested a spokesman of the anti-Israeli Palestinian radical
group Hamas.
</P>
<P>
Jordanian Minister of State for Information Affairs Samir
Mutawe today told the press that Ibrahim Ghosheh, the Amman-based
spokesman of Hamas, or the Islamic Resistance Movement, has been
arrested.
</P>
<P>
The minister did not give further information about the arrest
which closely followed a triple suicide bombing in Jerusalem last
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Hamas has claimed responsibility for the bomb attack, and a
previous dual bombing on July 30 in Jerusalem which killed 17
people.
</P>
<P>
The Thursday bombing, which killed seven people, overshadowed
the upcoming maiden trip by the United States' Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright to reactivate the stalled Middle East peace
process.
</P>
<P>
Jordan is one of the major mediators in the peace process. 
</P>
