<HEADLINE> Chinese, Romanian Presidents Hold Talks (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin,
meeting here today with Romanian President Emil Constantinescu,
said China is ready to join hands with Romania to lead a sound and
comprehensive Sino-Romanian friendship into the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
During the talks, the two leaders expressed their satisfaction
with the smooth development of bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that although the world's political situation has
fluctuated constantly in recent years and great changes have taken
place in China and Romania, the friendship between the two
countries has stood the test of time.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have seen frequent high-level contacts, and
supported each other and coordinated closely in international
affairs, he said, adding that bilateral relations have been
increasingly strengthened in politics, economics, culture, and
education.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president contributed the long-term Sino-Romanian
friendship to the efforts made by the two sides in overcoming
their differences in ideology and maintaining mutual respect,
equal treatment, mutual understanding and support.
</P>
<P>
He noted that China and Romania, without a radical conflict of
interests between them, share common goals of safeguarding world
peace and promoting economic development.
</P>
<P>
To uphold Sino-Romanian friendship is not only the consensus of
the leaders of the two countries but also the common aspiration of
their peoples, he added.
</P>
<P>
Jiang cited Romania as an important partner in the region of
the central and eastern Europe, saying that China has all along
attached great significance to developing relations with Romania.
</P>
<P>
China respects Romania's development road and its foreign and
domestic policies, and supports what it has done in maintaining
its independence, sovereignty and territorial integrity, he said.
</P>
<P>
China, he went on, is willing to develop a long-term, stable
and all-round relationship with Romania on the basis of the Five
Principles of Peaceful Co-existence.
</P>
<P>
Constantinescu said that Romania places great importance on its
ties with China and one of its foreign policy goals is to forge a
new, long-term and close partnership with China.
</P>
<P>
China is a great political and economic power in the world, he
said, and Romania hopes to tighten its links with China in these
areas, and hopes to understand China's views on some major issues
that face the people of the world, so as to make joint efforts for
the development of the humankind, he said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that Romania believes there is only one China in
the world and the People's Republic of China is the sole legal
government representing the Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
Romania keeps to the one China stand and will not establish
and develop any form of official ties with Taiwan, he added.
</P>
<P>
As for the Tibet issue, he said, Romania won't do anything to
harm the interests of the Chinese people.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
