<HEADLINE> Qing Dynasty Fort Found in South China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- A fort with two cannons from the
Qing Dynasty (1644-1911) has been found on a mountain top which
faces a famous waterfall in south China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The fort, with two-m-thick, 2.8-m-high stone walls, is located
on the top of Mount Yinpan, some 1,500 m above sea level, and
looks onto the Detian Waterfall.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that the fort was used to guard an area extending
10 km around the waterfall during the War of Resistance Against
the French Invaders (1884-1885). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970908.0029 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese, Romanian Presidents Hold Talks (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
On economic and trade relations, Jiang said the Chinese
Government attaches importance to the development of economic and
trade links with Romania.
</P>
<P>
He said that the two countries have a sound basis for economic
and trade links. Noting that the two countries have undergone
great changes in their economic and trade systems in recent years,
he said that both sides can adopt some practical and effective
measures to establish multi-level, multi-channel links and develop
flexible direct cooperation in all forms.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the two sides should actively explore all
forms of economic and technological cooperation and push forward
the progress of bilateral trade and economic relations.
</P>
<P>
Jiang expressed the convinction that he is confident that
through joint efforts, the two countries will be able to elevate
economic and trade cooperation to a new level.
</P>
<P>
Constantinescu briefed Jiang about Romania's economic growth
and its long-term plan for foreign trade and economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He acknowledged that the two countries have a great potential
for expanding economic and trade cooperation. He said that
relevant departments of the two countries will further explore new
forms and ways of cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Romania welcomes China to invest in the country, and Romania
holds that the expansion of economic and trade cooperation between
the two countries is in the interests of the two peoples, he added.
</P>
<P>
The two presidents also exchanged views on the international
situation, which Jiang said is undergoing enormous and profound
changes.
</P>
<P>
There is an accelerating tendency toward multi-polarization,
and the tendency toward independence and self-sufficiency is on
the rise in every country in the world, he said.
</P>
<P>
More and more countries have come to the same conclusion that
they should encourage dialogue and cooperation instead of
confrontation and conflict.
</P>
<P>
However, he said that there are still factors of instability
and that peace and development are facing challenges.
</P>
<P>
Noting that China pursues an independent foreign policy of
peace, Jiang said China and Romania have identical or similar
views on many major international issues, and China is ready to
continue to step up its discussion and cooperation with Romania on
international affairs.
</P>
<P>
Constantinescu said that Romania places importance on China's
role in the international community and its stance on major
international issues. He said that Romania is ready to regularly
exchange views on international issues and develop mutual support
with China.
</P>
<P>
Later in the evening, Jiang hosted a banquet in honor of
President Constantinescu and his party in the Great Hall of the
People. 
</P>
</TEXT>
