underground firearms workshop in Dhanusa district of central
Nepal, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Acting on a tip, the police raided the house of villager
Biswanath Sharma Lohar and recovered some materials for
manufacturing firearms.
</P>
<P>
Police confiscated four units of guns, four pistols and some
ammunition.
</P>
<P>
Lohar, 50, is alleged to have been involved in manufacturing
and trading firearms for several years.
</P>
<P>
He was detained along with his wife, two sons and one daughter,
reports said.  
