<HEADLINE> MCI Reduces State-to-State Calls to 5 Cents on Sundays </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The MCI Communications Inc.,
the second largest player in the U.S. telecommunication service,
said that it had reduced its Sunday rate on state-to-state
long-distance calls to 5 cents a minute, effective from September
7.
</P>
<P>
"Sunday is the day that Americans call the most," said John
Donoghue, MCI senior vice president of consumer marketing. "Every
MCI residential customer automatically receives the industry's
best long-distance rate -- 5 cents a minute -- on top of their
regular MCI savings."
</P>
<P>
The new rates also apply to calls to Canada.
</P>
<P>
It is unclear whether the AT&AMP;T Corporation, the Sprint
Corporation and other long-distance companies will offer similar
discounts.
</P>
<P>
MCI, headquartered in Washington, D.C., made its 1996 revenues
18.5 billion U.S. dollars. MCI is the world's third largest
carrier of international voice traffic.
</P>
<P>
By the end of this year MCI plans to merge with British Telecom
to form Concert, the world's first global communications company.
</P>
</TEXT>
