<HEADLINE> Xiamen Trade Fair Connected to Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese people now have
Internet access to information about the China Investment and
Trade Fair, which opened today in the Chinese coastal city of Xiamen.
</P>
<P>
The fair, which is held on September 8 every year, went on-line
Sunday, and the data is available on terminals and private
computers connected to Internet.
</P>
<P>
The information includes a general description of the fair,
invitations for investment, and a brief introduction of Xiamen and
Fujian province where Xiamen is. People can book hotel rooms and
find out where meetings are being held via the Internet.
</P>
<P>
Similar services were offered at last year's fair, but this
year's offerings cover a larger geographic area and the network's
capacity has been expanded.
</P>
<P>
This year, the fair was promoted to national status from its
former position as a regional business event. 
