<HEADLINE> Advanced Self-Service Bank Opens in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 8 (Xinhua) -- A self-service bank with the
most up-to-date technology opened today in Shanghai, the largest
industrial city and commercial center in China.
</P>
<P>
The new bank is a branch of the Industrial and Commercial Bank
of China (ICBC) and part of the ICBC's effort to improve its
services, according to sources with the bank.
</P>
<P>
Customers can get a thorough understanding of the bank's
offerings from a multimedia service, such as information on
exchange rates, deposits, card accounts and loan interest. It's
different from other banks of the kind because customers can make
transfers between authorized individuals' accounts.
</P>
<P>
There are four ATMs which are on-line with VISA/PLUS networks
and can handle foreign exchange cards, and two automatic
depositors that handle RMB yuan deposits.
</P>
<P>
The showpieces of the new bank are two automatic
money-changers, the most advanced in the city, which can be used
by foreign visitors to change foreign currencies into yuan in line
with the day's exchange rates.
</P>
<P>
The bank is open round-the-clock, but late-night customers will
have to use a Peony card to gain entrance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
