<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 9 (Xinhua) -- More than 1,000 publishers and
book traders from 45 countries attended the 10th Moscow
International Book Fair, which ended here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
During the fair, which opened last Wednesday, activities
included seminars, good book awards, and autograph parties were
organized.
</P>
<P>
The fair coincided with the celebrations marking the 850
anniversary of Moscow. It also featured a variety of new books on
the Russian capital city from 800 Russian publishers and
book-trading companies.
</P>
<P>
Also attending the fair were representatives from the China
International Book Trading Corporation and Press and Publication
Administration of China.
</P>
<P>
The two Chinese companies brought more than 300 books on
traditional Chinese painting, medicine and Chinese martial arts to
the fair.
</P>
<P>
The first Moscow International Book Fair was held in 1977. And
except for the year 1991, the fair has been held biennually. But
as of this year, it will become an annual event. 
</P>
