<HEADLINE> Six Regional Chinese Airliners Forge Alliance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Six regional airliners in
China today announced the establishment of the "New Star Aviation
Alliance" created to enhance their market-share.
</P>
<P>
The alliance is scheduled to become operational on January 1,
1998. It is the first such cooperation among local aviation
companies, according to official sources.
</P>
<P>
The six members are the Shenzhen Airliners, the Sichuan
Airliners, the Shandong Airliners, the Wuhan Airliners, the
Zhongyuan (Central China) Airliners and the Hainan Airliners.
</P>
<P>
It will be an informal partnership, as no changes will be made
to their relations with each other or their legal person status,
according to the announcement made in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The New Star will set up an integrated market- and
passenger-oriented transporting network to improve customer
service.
</P>
<P>
All New Star members will cooperate with each other in handling
passengers, sharing airport facilities and ticket booking offices,
and adopting the same codes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
