<HEADLINE> Beijing, HK Teachers Celebrate Teachers' Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- A delegation of teachers from
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region arrived here today to
celebrate the Teachers' Day with their Beijing colleagues.
</P>
<P>
The delegation consists of 15 members, most of them primary
and middle school teachers and headmasters. They were invited to
the capital city by the Beijing Municipal Education Commission.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from the Hong Kong SAR said at the event, held
in the Beijing No. Four Middle School, that they were honored to
be the first group of Hong Kong teachers to celebrate the special
day in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Teachers are respected by more and more people in Hong Kong,
and so is education, they noted.
</P>
<P>
Qiu Jilong, headmaster of the Beijing No. Four Middle School,
said that this year's Teachers' Day is the first held since Hong
Kong returned to its motherland, and it is of great significance
to have Hong Kong teachers here to enjoy the festivities with
Beijing teachers and students.
</P>
<P>
Although educational systems are different in Beijing and Hong
Kong, the same demands are made for teachers everywhere, such as
to be well-qualified and to set a good example for students, Qiu
added.
</P>
<P>
The delegation will visit the Tiananmen Square, the Hancunhe
Middle School and some teachers' families during their stay in
Beijing. 
</P>
