<HEADLINE> Catamaran Begins Service in East China City of Xiamen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Haichang, a speed
catamaran, on Sunday made its first voyage between Xiamen and
Dongshan Island, both in east China's Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
The Dongshan Huahong Speedy Shipping Co. Ltd. plans to use the
double-hulled vessel to transport the increasing number of
tourists to the scenic Dongshan Island.
</P>
<P>
Xiamen is a special economic zone and a popular tourist
destination. It is also one of the port cities that have plans to
open direct shipping across the Taiwan Strait.
</P>
<P>
Local officials expressed their hopes that the opening of the
catamaran service could lay a sound foundation for the forthcoming
direct shipping between the interior areas of China and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The route of the high-speed passenger boat is expected to be
extended to the city of Shantou in Guangdong Province,
south China, the officials said. 
