<HEADLINE> Li Peng Meets Saint Lucia Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- China is ready to develop
friendly cooperative ties with eastern Caribbean nations in line
with the five principles of peaceful co-existence, Chinese Premier
Li Peng said here today.
</P>
<P>
While meeting with George Odlum, Minister of Foreign
Affairs and International Trade of Saint Lucia, Li extended a warm
welcome to his guest and said he believed Odlum's current visit
would help promote the deepening of bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Odlum's visit, which has taken place soon after the
two countries established diplomatic ties, indicates that the
government of Saint Lucia attaches great importance to its
relations with China.
</P>
<P>
"Promotion of a friendly relationship of cooperation between
China and Saint Lucia, both developing nations, is in the
interests of the two peoples," the premier said.
</P>
<P>
"The establishment of diplomatic relations between China and
Saint Lucia is a major event in the history of bilateral ties," he
said. "This has laid a foundation for an overall development of
the relationship. China is ready to strengthen the relations of
mutual benefit and cooperation in various fields with Saint Lucia,
especially in the field of economic and trade cooperation and
exchanges."
</P>
<P>
Li said he appreciated the one-China policy of the new
government of Saint Lucia.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated that the Chinese government has always adopted
an independent foreign policy for peace and held that all
countries, no matter they are big or small, rich or poor,
strong or weak, should be on an equal footing.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Odlum said he was honored to meet Li and
passed on regards from Saint Lucia Prime Minister Kenny Anthony to
Li, who in return asked Odlum to convey his best wishes to
Anthony.
</P>
<P>
The decision by his new government to set up diplomatic ties
with China is an important one based on political principles,
Odlum said, adding it is also a major event in the history of
bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that Saint Lucia respects China's sovereignty and
sticks to the one-China principle.
</P>
<P>
He said his government spoke highly of China's foreign policy,
adding that China, as a big country, treats a small country like
Saint Lucia in a broadminded way.
</P>
<P>
"We appreciate it very much," he said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the friendship between China and Saint Lucia is
sincere.
</P>
<P>
After the two countries established diplomatic ties, their
bilateral relations have become stronger, and the ties between
China and other eastern Caribbean states have also been promoted,
he said.
</P>
<P>
Present at today's meeting were Liu Huaqiu, director of the
Foreign Affairs Office of the State Council, and Li Zhaoxing,
Vice-Foreign Minister.  
</P>
</TEXT>
