<HEADLINE> Australia-China Forum Opens In Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Economic and trade cooperation
between China and Australia have become one of the most salient
features of bilateral relations, a senior Chinese official said
here today.
</P>
<P>
Song Jian, state councillor and minister in charge of the State
Science and Technology Commission, told the third session of the
Australia China Forum that trade and economic links between the
two countries have been growing fast since they forged diplomatic
ties 25 years ago.
</P>
<P>
He said he is fully confident that the links will be further
expanded in the next 25 years. He also wished the forum a complete
success.
</P>
<P>
Australian Deputy Prime Minister and Minister for Trade Tim
Fischer opened the meeting by saying that Australia regards its
tie with China as one of its four most important foreign
relationships.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Australian Government is geared up to develop
multi-faceted engagement and cooperation with China.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he expressed the hope that cooperative relations
between the two countries will keep strengthening in the next 25
century and handed down through generations.
</P>
<P>
The bi-annual forum is co-sponsored by the Chinese Ministry of
Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation (MOFTEC) and the Australian
Trade Commission (Austrade). This session, held under the title
"Australia China Forum '97 -- 25 years," has drawn over 300
business people and government officials from both countries.
