<HEADLINE> Zambia Appreciates Peaceful Solution to Korean </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, September 8 (Xinhua) -- President Frederick Chiluba
has said Zambia appreciates and recognizes the commitments of the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) toward finding a
peaceful solution to the crisis in the Korean peninsula.
</P>
<P>
In a message sent to his DPRK counterpart Kim Song-Il at the
weekend to mark the country's 49 anniversary tuesday, President
Chiluba expressed his hope that DPRK will continue to work toward
attaining a peaceful solution to the conflict between Pyongyang
and Seoul.
</P>
<P>
The two Koreas fought a large-scale war in the early 1950s in
which both the U.S. and China were deeply involved. Their
hostility has not diminished with the end of the cold war.
</P>
<P>
Chiluba stressed that the attainment of peace in the peninsula
will have far reaching ramification on the world peace.
</P>
<P>
He added that Zambia cherished the warm and long standing
relations that exist between the two countries and hoped the the
relations will be further enhanced for the mutual benefits of
DPRK and Zambia.
</P>
<P>
The Zambian president also wished the prosperity of the DPRK
and its people. 
