<HEADLINE> Guangdong Province Expands Overseas Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Overseas enterprises run by
south China's Guangdong Province in south China are engaging in
competition on the world market and in turn contributing greatly
to the province's economic growth.
</P>
<P>
The province has established 862 firms in 48 countries and
regions, some 50 percent of which are in Hong Kong. These
enterprises recorded a business volume of over 70 billion yuan
last year in ventures in the trade, industrial, finance,
labor and consulting services sectors.
</P>
<P>
Participation in international competition has greatly promoted
the performance and efficiency of local enterprises. The Hong Kong
Branch of the Glee Group, after considering the needs of the
European market, has decided to introduce a production line
of mobile air-conditioners.
</P>
<P>
Five Guangdong businesses are currently listed on the Hong Kong
stock exchange. The Yuehai Group, formed with an investment of two
million US dollars, had total assets of 21.7 billion Hong Kong
dollars by the end of 1995, with its assets growing by an average
73 percent annually.
</P>
<P>
The province has led the nation in terms of imports and exports
over the past 12 years, with overseas businesses from Guandong
contributing greatly to the notable success. 
</P>
