<HEADLINE> OIC Secretary-General Talks with Iranian FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The Secretary-General of the
Organization of Islamic Conference (OIC) Izzidine Al-Iraki met
with Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal Kharrazi here today to
discuss ways of holding the 8th OIC summit here in December.
</P>
<P>
"Tehran summit will be a turning point in the ties among
the Islamic countries, and considering the Islamic countries' keen
interest in attending the meeting in Tehran, it is hoped
that this summit will be able to resolve the problems of the
Islamic world," Iraki was quoted by the state-run Tehran Radio
as saying.
</P>
<P>
Iraki, who arrived here yesterday, expressed the willingness of
his office to cooperate with Iran during Iran's chairmanship of
the OIC which begins this December.
</P>
<P>
Morocco is presently chairing the OIC which was founded in May
1971 and has a total 42 member states.
</P>
<P>
"During Iran's chairmanship of OIC, the Secretariat and all
the people running this organization will have serious cooperation
and coordination with the Islamic Republic of Iran," he added.
</P>
<P>
Kharrazi urged OIC to take a more active part in solving
the problems of the Muslims which, he said, constituted some
25 percent of the world population.
</P>
<P>
"In the post-cold war world, which is no longer bipolar
and in which the regional and international organizations are
increasingly spending efforts to be present in world equations,
it is necessary for the OIC ... to play a more definitive
role in resolving world problems," he said. 
</P>
