<HEADLINE> Railcar-Truck Collision Kills 12 in Southwest France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 8 (Xinhua) -- A railcar collided today with a
fuel oil truck in Port-Sainte-Foy, southwest France, killing 12
people.
</P>
<P>
About 30 others were injured, including 10 in serious
condition, in what is the worst railway accident in France for
years, Agence France-Presse (AFP) said.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government of Dordogne sent four helicopters and
a dozen ambulances in an emergency rescue operation.
</P>
<P>
The railcar of the state railway company SNCF was running from
Libourne in the department of Gironde to Sarlat in the department
of Dordogne.
</P>
<P>
The grade crossing where the accident took place is controlled
by automatic flash lights and not supervised by SNCG employees,
said the AFP.
</P>
<P>
The SNCF said it did not know whether the automatic control
signals were working normally when the accident happened. 
</P>
