<HEADLINE> Traffic Accident Leaves 7 People Dead in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, September 8 (Xinhua) -- A traffic accident has left
seven people dead and several others wounded in northwestern
Zambia when the van they were traveling in careered off the road
and plunged into a river.
</P>
<P>
Zambia News Agency reported today that the accident occurred
on the road between Solwezi, 350 kilometers northwest of Lusaka,
and another northwestern city Mwinilunga last Friday night when
they were traveling from Solwezi to Mwinilunga.
</P>
<P>
A police spokesman who confirmed the accident said that the
Toyota van with 14 passengers on board careered off the road and
threw some passengers on the tarmac before plunging into the
Kabompo river with some other passengers.
</P>
<P>
Seven people died in nearby hospitals. Among them, there are a
two-year old child and a pregnant woman, said the spokesman,
adding the driver is still missing.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman did not spell out the cause of the accident.
</P>
