<HEADLINE> US Should Stop Tobacco Export: WHO </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The World Health
Organization (WHO) has appealed to the United States to prevent
American companies from exporting tobacco to developing
countries, local daily Sowetan reported today.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from 49 African states made the appeal in a
draft resolution reached at a five-day WHO African Regional
Committee's 47 session concluded at the weekend at Sun City in
Northwest Province.
</P>
<P>
They unanimously agreed to urge the WHO secretariat to support
African countries to put in place effective tobacco control
measures.
</P>
<P>
The anti-tobacco resolution was strengthened by research
results that by the year 2030, 10 million deaths globally would be
related to tobacco use, and most of these fatalities would occur
in developing countries. 
</P>
