<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Open Policy Benefits Northeast China Liaoning Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Liaoning
Province has witnessed an economic upsurge in recent years as a
result of expanded opening and the rise of booming export-oriented
businesses.
</P>
<P>
Some 80 percent of the total overseas investment used in the
province since its opening to the outside in 1978 came in
the past five years. Much of the investments have been
earmarked for the transformation of outmoded state-owned
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The province has also recorded double-digit foreign trade
growth over the past five years, with last year's total volume
topping 15 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The coastal city of Dalian, which leads in the local opening
efforts, has notched further progress in the construction of
development and free trade zones. More than 20 international
financial organizations have opened offices in Dalian and have
helped the city to emerge as one of northern China's major trade,
commercial and financial center.
</P>
<P>
Booming export-oriented economic development in Shenyang, the
provincial capital, and Jinzhou have played an important role in
accelerating the province's comprehensive economic prosperity.
</P>
<P>
In addition to focusing on infrastructure construction, the
province has also emphasized improvements in the local investment
environment and introduced improved legal and professional
training systems.. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
