<HEADLINE> Nigeria to Hold International Tourism Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Nigerian capital Abuja is to
hold its first international travel market fair on December 3,
the Guardian newspaper reported today.
</P>
<P>
Head of the organizing group, Sola Ilupeju was quoted as
saying that seven countries, including the Benin Republic, Togo,
Turkey, Romania, Israel, China and Democratic People's Republic
of Korea have agreed to participate.
</P>
<P>
At least 30 Nigerian firms have also shown interest, he said.
</P>
<P>
Ilupeju expressed the hope that the fair will help promote
Abuja as the best destination for conference and vacations in
west Africa and the world at large.
</P>
<P>
It is also his wish that the fair will showcase the tourism
industry as an export industry which urgently needs government
support and patronage.
</P>
<P>
According to the organizer, the fair has received its
preliminary endorsement from the tourism sub-committee of the
Vision 2010 Committee.
</P>
<P>
Ilupeju claimed that some hotels in Abuja, including Nicon
Noga Hilton, Sheraton and Rockview have agreed to offer 50
percent discount to participants at the fair for one week.
</P>
</TEXT>
