<HEADLINE> Computer System Breaks Down on Russia's Mir Station </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The main computer system on
Russia's Mir space station broke down, resulting in a shutdown of
all systems except life-support functions, a Russian space official
said today.
</P>
<P>
The computer shut itself off for unknown reasons, said Valery
Lyndin, spokesman for Russia's Mission Control.
</P>
<P>
"The computer has become capricious again," and the time when
it happened was not clear, he added.
</P>
<P>
The crew on board, two Russian cosmonauts and one American
astronaut, were not in any immediate danger, the Associated Press
quoted Lyndin as saying.
</P>
<P>
The computer system had failed twice in recent months, which
took the crew "several days to fully restore all functions," the
reported. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
