<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue to Rise on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to
rise in active trading on the Singapore market as the benchmark
Straits Times Industrials Index gained another 7.87 points to
close at 1891.93 today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume increased to 467.26 million units,
valued at 772.16 million Singapore dollars (about 511.36 million
U.S. dollars). Advances overwhelmed declines by 329 to 47, while
233 other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Rekapac was the most actively traded stock as it registered a
turnover of 28.54 million units. It was followed by the Asia Food
&AMP; Property which had 24.15 million shares traded. Ber Group was
next with 21.39 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Local property giant Oriental Holdings led the gainers of the
day as it rose 1.6 dollars to finish at 6.9 Singapore dollars.
Computer sound card maker Creative 50 increased 1.5 dollars to end
at 34.1 Singapore dollars. The Thai Prime Fund was 75 cents higher
to close at seven U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, the Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign and
WantWant shared the top spot on the losers' list as each of them
declined 40 cents to end at 23.5 Singapore dollars and three U.S.
dollars respectively. Local food and soft drinks maker F&AMP;N fell 30
cents to close at 9.1 Singapore dollars, while Hume finished 28
cents lower at 3.7 dollars.  
