<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Hovers near 73 U.S. Cents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar today
hovered around 73.00 U.S. cents as market players awaited jobs
figures due out on Thursday to provide further direction.
</P>
<P>
The local currency ended at 72.98 U.S. cents, down from its
late Friday level of 73.24.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the Australian dollar spent the day between 72.92
and 73.09 U.S. cents.
</P>
<P>
Players said they were watching for Thursday's Australian
Bureau of Statistics August labor force data release to determine
the chances of a cut to official interest rates.
</P>
<P>
Economist Glenn Maguire said that a strong employment outcome
should cement the view that monetary policy was on hold for the
time being.
</P>
<P>
"The risk to interest rate markets this week, however, is a
combination of weak housing and employment data, prompting the
market to again reassess the likely stance of monetary policy," he
said.
</P>
<P>
On the cross-rates, the Australian dollar finished at 88.12
from 88.66 against the Japanese yen and at 1.3116 from 1.3202
against the German mark.  
