<HEADLINE> Three Killed by Lightening on Golf Course </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Three people were killed and two
injured by lightning on a golf course in northern central Japan
on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Two golfers Yoshiaki Katori, 56, Atsushi Takayasu, 31, and
female caddy Yoshie Kishi, 53, died instantly after being attacked
by a lightning bolt in Ibaraki prefecture, 75 kilometers north of
Tokyo.
</P>
