<DOCNO> XIE19970908.0131 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India Not Able to Buy Nuclear Plants: IAEA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Chief of the International
Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) Hans Blix said today that India would
not be able to buy nuclear plants as long as it remains outside
Non-Proliferation Treaty (NPT).
</P>
<P>
Talking to newsmen here after inaugurating the international
seminar on the role of nuclear energy for sustainable development
organized by the Department of Atomic Energy, Hans Blix said that
since most vendors of nuclear plants belong to nuclear suppliers
club, they are prohibited from selling nuclear technologies to
countries that do not accept IAEA fullscope safeguards.
</P>
<P>
India was able to go ahead with its nuclear deal with Russia
because the deal was struck before Russia was bound by the new
control regime, he further said.
</P>
<P>
Apart from finance, the single major hurdle for India to
develop its nuclear power program is its non-adherence to NPT, he
added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970908.0132 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Employment Woes Worst in Five Years in South Korea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, September 8 (Xinhua) -- With the number of job seekers
exceeding that of the available jobs, South Korea will likely have
its worst year in employment this year since 1992, according to
government officials.
</P>
<P>
The number of the unemployed in July reached 14,587 while
vacant positions were only 13,785, according to the Ministry of
Finance and Economy (MOFE) and the Ministry of Labor.
</P>
<P>
These figures were collected from 52 employment security
centers across the country.
</P>
<P>
This marks the first time that the number of job seekers has
surpassed the number of available jobs since 1992. The resulting
low rate of job availability for this year is an outcome of the
ongoing economic recession and the bankruptcies of major
conglomerates, officials said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
