<HEADLINE> CCP 15th Congress to Lay Good Foundation for Future: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Former Australian Prime
Minister Malcolm Fraser said today the upcoming 15th Chinese
Communist Party (CCP) Congress will lay a good foundation for
China's future social and economic development.
</P>
<P>
"I wish the Chinese people well and the congress a success,"
the former prime minister said in Melbourne today.
</P>
<P>
The party congress is scheduled to open Friday and is expected
to make strategic plans on the country's future development and
elect a party leadership leading China into the next century.
</P>
<P>
Under the leadership of the Chinese Communist Party, China will
go forward "in its own way" to modernization and prosperity,
Fraser said in a telephone interview with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
He expressed optimism about the future of the world's most
populous country and fastest economy in the world.
</P>
<P>
Fraser said his optimism was based upon China's experience
during the past 18 years' reform and opening to the outside world
under the leadership of the party.
</P>
<P>
Great achievements have been made in China's economic and
social development since the reform and opening policy was
initiated 18 years ago, said Fraser, who had been prime minister
during November of 1975 and March of 1983.
</P>
<P>
China's economy has been growing at an average of 10 percent
each year during the past 18 years.
</P>
<P>
He attributed the success to the particular road China chose
under the leadership of the party, which helped improve the
standard of living of hundreds of millions of people.
</P>
<P>
China's rapid development and stability is favorable to other
part of the world, and China's huge domestic market, particularly
the potential purchasing power of 1.2 billion consumers, provides
great opportunities for other countries, including Australia.
</P>
<P>
He hoped China will join the World Trade Organization "as soon
as possible".  
</P>
</TEXT>
