<HEADLINE> French President to Visit Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 8 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
will pay an official visit to Russia from September 25 to 27 at
the invitation of Russian President Boris Yeltsin, said the Elysee
presidential office today.
</P>
<P>
This will be the second visit by Chirac to Moscow this year.
</P>
<P>
He visited Russia in early February, during which he discussed
with Yeltsin the elaboration of a charter on bilateral relations
between Russia and the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO).
</P>
<P>
The charter was adopted in May in Paris by Russia and NATO,
which was supposed to provide a framework for building a
partnership between the two sides while allowing NATO to absorb
new members from the former Warsaw Pact bloc.
</P>
<P>
French Foreign Minister Hubert Vedrine will pay a brief visit
to Moscow this week to meet his Russian counterpart Yevgeni
Primakov, said French officials. 
</P>
