<HEADLINE> Ancient Relics Discovered in Liaoning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Some 30 iron, bronze and
pottery relics dating back to the Western Han Dynasty (206 BC-24
AD) were recently unearthed in Xiuyan County, northeast China's
Liaoning province.
</P>
<P>
The relics include gray pottery pieces, iron agricultural
implements such as spades and sickles, bronze arrow heads and
tiles.
</P>
<P>
The relics, discovered on the construction site for a new
village government building, reflect the life of local people some
2,000 years ago, according to Chinese archeologists.  
</P>
