<HEADLINE> Beijing Opens 100th Museum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The number of museums in
Beijing, the Chinese capital, hit 100 with the recent opening of
the Beijing Traditional Opera Museum.
</P>
<P>
The museum, located on Hufangqiao in the Xuanwu District,
houses precious historical data, cultural relics and audio-visual
materials of traditional operas in Beijing, especially materials
on Peking Opera.
</P>
<P>
"Beijing Daily" reports that the museum will also focus on the
research and promotion of the traditional operas. It will also
host traditional operas performances.
</P>
<P>
Beijing has only had two museums in 1949 -- the Palace Museum
and a history museum. Today, however, the city ranks second in the
country with one museum for every 120,000 people, a level six
times higher than the national average.
</P>
<P>
The city's museums host between 30-40 million Chinese and
foreign visitors annually. 
</P>
</TEXT>
