<HEADLINE> Provinces in South China To Jointly Build Wholesale Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Four provinces in south
China will jointly build a farm produce wholesale market in order
to upgrade the national farm produce distribution network.
</P>
<P>
The market will be Located in Zengcheng, Guangdong Province. It
will offer both spot and futures trading, as well as the
international practice of agency services.
</P>
<P>
Experts note that the market will greatly improve the
distribution system which has long hinder development of the
nation's agricultural sector.
</P>
<P>
The market, which will cover 190,000 sq.m., is expected to
become a major farm produce distribution hub in south China, as
well as a sideline produce center serving Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong, Jiangxi, Hunan and Hainan provinces will establish
the market at a cost of five billion yuan (602.4 million US
dollars). The project has also won strong support from the
government of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region. 
</P>
