<HEADLINE> Guangdong Province to Modernize Villages, Towns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 8 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong
province has accelerated its efforts to modernize local villages and
towns in order to further improve the living conditions of rural
residents.
</P>
<P>
Plans through the year 2000 require that rules and regulations be
formulated for the construction and management of villages and
towns, including building roads linking villages and urban areas,
improving water supply systems, and establishing sewage and waste
water disposal centers.
</P>
<P>
"Ninety-five percent of the rural towns will have water supply,
and rubbish disposal facilities, and well over half of the
province's rural areas will have access to sanitary public toilet
facilities by the turn of the century," provincial Vice-Governor
Tang Bingquan has said.
</P>
<P>
This is aimed at matching the rural living conditions to the
economic development of the province and further improving the
ecological environment and implementing the sustainable development
strategy, he added.
</P>
<P>
He also called for such relatively developed areas as the
Zhujiang River Delta to set examples in building rural living
quarters, rural gardens and roads for other areas to follow, the
Vice-governor noted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
