<HEADLINE> Heilongjiang Promoting Foreign Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Heilongjiang Province, a
landlocked province in northeast China, has witnessed a boom of
foreign trade over the past decade.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the province has used over two billion US
dollars of foreign funds since 1987, and has participate in 1,600
technological cooperation projects with overseas counterparts.
</P>
<P>
More than six million people living in 20-odd border cities and
counties have escaped the yokes of poverty following
implementation of the reform and opening policies. Local
authorities also note a dozen-fold increase in annual per capita
income.
</P>
<P>
The province's border imports and exports reached 6.6 billion
US dollars during the 1987-1996 period. 
