<HEADLINE> OPEC to Provide Bangladesh With Loan for Railway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The OPEC Fund for International
Development will provide Bangladesh with 15 million U.S. dollars
for the construction of a railway over the Jamuna Bridge, a
private news agency reported here today.
</P>
<P>
An agreement on the loan was signed by Bangladesh and the OPEC
fund in Vienna on August 22, the United News of Bangladesh (UNB)
said, adding that the loan is to co-finance the railway with the
Asian Development Bank.
</P>
<P>
The loan will have an interest rate of 2 percent, a repayment
period of 12 years and a grace period of five years.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the construction of a 99-kilometer dual-gauge
rail track, the OPEC loan will also be used for the conversion of
a 250-kilometer existing track to connect and standardize the
railway networks on either side of the bridge, which are currently
running on different gauges, the UNB said.
</P>
<P>
In the past, the OPEC fund provided this South-Asian country
with loans amounting to 224.86 million dollars, out of which
project assistance was 164.14 million dollars and commodity
assistance 60.02 million dollars, the UNB noted.
</P>
<P>
Besides, four new projects involving 107 million dollars in
rural electrification and rural infrastructure sectors are under
active consideration by the OPEC fund for financing.  
</P>
</TEXT>
