<HEADLINE> Pakistan to Install Pollution Monitoring System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan government has
decided to install an air pollution monitoring system in the
capital and other major cities to gauge ratio of air pollution,
officials said today.
</P>
<P>
A vigorous campaign is also being launched all over the country
against pollution and to create awareness against smoke, noise,
industrial waste and other types of pollution among the people,
the officials said.
</P>
<P>
The National Assembly has recently approved a legislation
providing for the protection, conservation, rehabilitation and
improvement of environment in the country.
</P>
<P>
This legislation, the officials said, would enable the
government to establish special tribunals to award punishment for
violation of its provisions.
</P>
<P>
The problem of environmental pollution in Pakistan has been
gradually becoming acute primarily because of increasing
industrial waste.
</P>
<P>
During the past two decades, the ratio of forests in the
country has also dwindled considerably due to indiscriminate
cutting of trees in the mountainous areas.  
</P>
</TEXT>
