<HEADLINE> International Anti-Corruption Conference Opens in Lima </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The eighth international
anti-corruption conference opened here today, expecting to
emphasize public participation in the fight against one of the
serious social evils in the world.
</P>
<P>
The conference was attended by representatives from more than
80 countries and regions and world organizations.
</P>
<P>
Inaugurating the conference, Peruvian President Alberto
Fujimori called for developing "a culture of faith" while
combating corruption.
</P>
<P>
Fujimori said that people's efforts for peace, development and
a better life were wasted as a result of corruption and
embezzlement of huge public funds.
</P>
<P>
Accepting kickbacks, taking bribes and power abuse should be
considered as "monsters that swallow up the public funds which
could have been used to create a bright future," he said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the need to promote moral education for teenagers
in the battle against corruption.
</P>
<P>
Feng Tiyun, head of the Chinese delegation attending the
conference, who is a vice-minister of the Chinese Ministry of
Supervision, said on the occasion that since introducing reform
and opening-up policies, China has laid emphasis on the combat
against corruption while carrying out economic construction, and
has thus made remarkable progress in coordinating its economic and
social development.
</P>
<P>
During the conference which will end on Thursday, the
participants will exchange their experience in fighting
corruption. 
</P>
