<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hungarian Advertisement Law Protects Children </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, September 7 (Xinhua) -- A new Hungarian law that has
come into effect this month bans any advertisement that is harmful
to children.
</P>
<P>
The law on advertisements approved in June is largely dedicated
to the protection of children from harmful effects of commercial
ads in order to ensure their healthy growth.
</P>
<P>
Under the law, children and youngsters are not allowed to
appear in ads related to scenes involving danger, violence and sex.
</P>
<P>
It also stipulates that no kids or non-adults shall appear on
cigarette or alcohol commercials. Such advertisements are
forbidden in and near educational institutions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
