<HEADLINE> 167 Die on Indian Roads Every Day: Newspaper </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 8 (Xinhua) -- With 29 million vehicles on
Indian roads, 167 people die every day due to road accidents in
the country, the Hindustan Times said today.
</P>
<P>
These startling facts were brought out in a recent two-day
state conference being organized by the East Delhi Branch of the
Indian Medical Association and Department of Neurosurgery at the
G.B. Pant Hospital, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
The majority of the deaths due to road accidents were
preventable, but due to poor transportation facility, non-existent
information and communication network and poorly maintained
hospitals, people died, the paper quoted President of the Indian
Medical Association-East Dr. Ashwini Malhotra as saying.
</P>
<P>
A coordinated effort is needed at various levels to reduce the
incidence of preventable mortality, Dr. Daljeet Singh said.
</P>
