<HEADLINE> Key Infrastructure Projects in South China Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The construction of two berths
for 10,000-dwt ships commenced recently at Fangcheng Harbor, in
south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The project, one of the 50 key ones scheduled for construction
under the annual regional plan for 1997, will be built at a cost
of 14.5 billion yuan, with the central government providing 7.38
billion yuan and the remainder coming from the local government.
</P>
<P>
The region completed a number of projects during the first
half of this year, including an expressway linking Guilin, a major
scenic site, and liuzhou, the installation of a generating unit at
the Jingnan Hydropower Station and the Nanning-Kunming Railway.
</P>
<P>
Over the next four months, Guangxi will concentrate on the
construction of thermal power plants in Laibin and Beihai, an
expressway and a major highway, a power transform project, a key
water conservancy project and a number of industrial projects.
</P>
<P>
The regional government's five-year plan calls for the
allocation of 200 billion yuan for the construction of some 350
key projects in the 1996-2000 period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
