<HEADLINE> Beijing Announces Ethical Standards for College Students </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing authorities
recently announced ethical standards for 190,000 university
students studying in the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
The standards stipulate that the students should love the
motherland and the city, seek truth from facts, study diligently,
and practice courtesy and thrift.
</P>
<P>
Students were recently called on to pledge to firmly abide by
the requirements.
</P>
<P>
Chairpersons of student unions in 67 universities and colleges
have vowed to follow the pledge.
</P>
<P>
