<BODY>
<HEADLINE> TV Manufacturers Merge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua)-- Two major Chinese electronics
companies have adopted the merger strategy to ensure their mutual
survival in the increasingly competitive market.
</P>
<P>
The TCL group based in South China's Guangdong Province and
Meile Electronics Co. Ltd. in North China's Henan Province jointly
established the Henan TCL and Meile Electronics Company. The new
company will manufacture both TCL and Meile brands color TVs,
according to a recent issue of "China Electronics News".
</P>
<P>
The company will become the first in China's color TV
manufacturing sector to produce two brands of color televisions.
</P>
<P>
Local economic analysts believe the establishment of the
company has set a new model in terms of state-owned
enterprises integration and the cooperation between firms in the
country's coastal and inland areas.
</P>
<P>
The new joint venture, based in Henan Province, has a total
registered capital of 115 million yuan and plans to produce one
million color TV sets annually during a cooperative term of 50
years.
</P>
<P>
TCL group, which holds a 52 percent of the joint venture
capital, and the Meile Corp. are both on the list of China's 50
most competitive electronics companies.
</P>
<P>
Since last spring, many of the nation's color TV producers have
lowered prices to gain a greater share of the highly competitive
market. The Changhong Group, China's largest color TV
manufacturer, reduced prices for its series of products by some
8-18 percent.
</P>
<P>
A 25-inch color TV currently costs around 3,000 yuan, down
some 1,300 yuan, or about 30 percent on the price in 1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
