<DOCNO> XIE19970908.0216 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italian President Calls for Unity Against Secession </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Italian President Oscar Luigi
Scalfaro today expressed support for the Italian government's
warnings to the country's secessionist Northern League against
holding self-styled Padania elections later this autumn.
</P>
<P>
The league, led by Umberto Bossi, has agitated for the
secession of the wealthy northern region in Italy which it calls
Padania and has announced parliament elections in Padania on
October 26.
</P>
<P>
Italian Prime Minister Romano Prodi warned last week that the
government might call in the legal authorities if the organization
persisted with its plans. But Bossi threatened immediately to use
the courts against political opponents.
</P>
<P>
Scalfaro said Prodi "was right to warn citizens that what is
planned for the October election is something outside and against
the constitution."
</P>
<P>
Prodi and nine of his ministers visited the northeastern region
of Veneto in Italy Saturday, a stronghold of the league, to spread
the unity message.
</P>
<P>
He said in a speech that "there is really no room for those who
divide. The process that is going on in Europe is one of
integration, not disintegration."
</P>
<P>
Scalfaro called for the "commitment of the people to work
together in harmony to move the country forward on the road to
civilization." 
</P>
</TEXT>
