<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Government Sets up Economic Command Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 8 (Xinhua) -- he Thai government has decided
to set up a national command center, effective today, to deal with
economic problems.
</P>
<P>
The center, to be staffed around the clock, will draw together
all the economic ministers, who will work as a team at the center
so as to shorten the line of command.
</P>
<P>
There will be a briefing of the economic situation every
morning at the center. And if a decision is to be made
immediately, it will be made there, the Bangkok Post today quotes
Prime Minister Chavalit Yongchaiyudh as saying.
</P>
<P>
The center will also draw advice from businessmen and experts,
Chavalit said.
</P>
<P>
He added that he would head the center and would try to attend
the daily briefing for a month.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
