<DOCNO> XIE19970908.0227 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 1st Thai-made Satellite to Be Launched in November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The first Thai-made
micro-satellite is scheduled to be launched in Russia in November,
the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The 150-kilogram satellite will be delivered to Russia within
three weeks, waiting for the launching by a zenith rocket of the
Russian Space Agency at Baikonur Cosmodrome.
</P>
<P>
The satellite was built by Thai engineers at the University of
Surrey in Britain and it will operate in a low-earth orbit to
monitor forest fires and water pollution and forecast weather.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
