<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hebei To Use Ten Billion US Dollars of Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Hebei Province in north China
is set to bring in ten billion US dollars of foreign investment
during the Ninth Five-Year Plan period (1996-2000), it was
announced at a press conference held here today.
</P>
<P>
The press briefing was sponsored by the Hebei delegation
attending the first China Investment and Trade Fair.
</P>
<P>
Bordering on the capital city of Beijing and the leading port
city of Tianjin, Hebei covers an area of 187,700 sq km, and has a
population of more than 64 million.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics, the province reported a gross domestic
product of 344.5 billion yuan (about 43 billion US dollars) in the
year 1996, ranking sixth among all provinces in the country.
</P>
<P>
Hebei used 1.6 billion US dollars of foreign investment last
year. By the end of last June, the province had received an
accumulated foreign investment of 5.711 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
There are more than 5,400 foreign-funded enterprises and joint
ventures in the province, involving energy, communications,
telecommunications, raw materials, textiles, electronics,
clothing, and processing of agricultural products.
</P>
<P>
During the Ninth Five-Year Plan, Hebei's investment in fixed
assets is expected to reach more than 1,000 billion yuan, and the
construction of a group of infrastructure projects will be sped up.
</P>
<P>
Foreign funding will be focused on the construction of
infrastructure projects such as water resources, energy, ports,
airports, and telecommunications, and the development of its six
pillar industries, metallurgy, building materials, chemicals,
machinery, electronics, and food.
</P>
<P>
During the fair, the delegation will list nearly 2,000 projects
for overseas financing, 150 of which are provincial-level key
projects.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
