<HEADLINE> Cyprus Beats Luxembourg 3-1 in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Ioannis Ioannou scored twice
in the second half to lead Cyprus' 3-1 victory over Luxembourg in
a meaningless World Cup qualifying match in Luxembourg on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Ioannou socred in the 55th and 80th minutes to break a 1-1
halftime tie, giving Cyprus its second victory in European Group
5.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus holds a 2-1-4 record and Luxembourg has lost all seven
games.
</P>
<P>
The two sides meet again October 11 in Cyprus. 
