<HEADLINE> Spectacular River-Damming To Boost Business, Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YICHANG, September 8 (Xinhua) -- A series of trade and tourism
activities will be conducted before and after the river-damming of
the Three Gorges Hydro-Power Project, in the city of Yichang, the
site of the multi-billion-dollar Project.
</P>
<P>
The activities are to be held From September 18 to November 23,
Yichang Deputy Mayor Zhang Jianyi told Xinhua today.
</P>
<P>
Local authorities are determined to turn the coming
river-damming into a good opportunity for boosting trade and
tourism, the deputy mayor said.
</P>
<P>
The damming is to begin in early November, paving the way for
the second phase of the main part of the dam project.
</P>
<P>
The official disclosed that a large number of overseas visitors
are expected to visit the city during the period, including over
100 foreign diplomatic envoys to China, a French entrepreneurs'
delegation and a 400-member group of tourists from Hong Kong and
Macao.
</P>
<P>
A number of meetings, commodity fairs and trade talks will also
be held in the city during the business and tourism promotion
period. The '97 China Central and Western Areas Investment and
Development Symposium has been scheduled on November 23. 
</P>
