<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hainan Firms Introduce Democratic Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Hainan province, China's
southernmost province, introduced democratic public elections
since 1993 to replace decades-old appointment practices in 182
state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The election process has since contributed greatly to the
rejuvenation of the enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Leaders in state companies were formerly nominated by higher
authorities. The new democratic system has created new way to
foster professional entrepreneurs capable of meeting the needs of
the modern enterprise system.
</P>
<P>
All elected leaders must fulfill their responsibilities in line
with contracts signed with employees. The new system forces
factory managers to fully consider the best interest of their
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
A recent survey revealed that some 57.9 percent of 160 formerly
loss-making companies are not turning profits, with the remaining
also recording various levels of improvement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970908.0236 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Spikers Enter Top Four at Asian Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DOHA, Qatar, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Chinese spikers sailed
into top four of Asian Volleyball Championships after trouncing
South Korea 3-0 on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team, led by former star Wang Jiawei, dominated the
match with tight blockings and powerful attackings. The set
scores were 15-4, 15-6 and 15-5 in favor of the Chinese team.
</P>
<P>
On Saturday, the Chinese team beat Pakistan 3-0 for their first
victory in the championships.
</P>
<P>
The South Korean team, which suffered a 0-3 defeat to Australia
on Saturday, failed to qualify for the last four for the first
time in the history of Asian Championships.
</P>
<P>
The South Koreans had won two championships titles and finished
runners-up three times in the previous editions of the Asian
Championships.
</P>
<P>
Australia and Japan also entered the single round-robin
semi-finals. The last semi-finalists will be either Chinese
Taipei or Iran. 
</P>
</TEXT>
