<DOCNO> XIE19970908.0241 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Expert Designs Future Stock Trading Web In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Consider this scenario: One
morning in the future, an investor reads data from the previous
day's stock trading on his PC, then logs on to the computerized
stock trading system to buy or sell stocks.
</P>
<P>
And when he travels, he keeps close tabs on the stock market
using his portable computer notebook, counting his gains and
losses or exchanging views with other investors via e-mail.
</P>
<P>
Chinese computer expert Deng Yihui says all this and more will
soon be a reality in China.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a recent international financial conference held in
Shanghai, the leading financial hub in the country, Deng called
for the acceleration of the networking of China's stock market,
and said he has just the plan to get it started.
</P>
<P>
China has a sound foundation for expanding its stock business
through the information web, Deng said, noting the country's stock
markets adopted the then-most advanced computerized telecom-webs
for automatic trading when they were set up.
</P>
<P>
The securities business has taken the lead in the country's
information revolution so as to meet the requirements of the
fast-developing stock market, he said.
</P>
<P>
According to the expert, there were over 100,000 computers in
the country operating synchronously on trading days to become one
of the largest computer networks in the world.
</P>
<P>
However, the existing network is far from satisfying the needs
of millions of Chinese investors who are eager to obtain
sufficient, authoritative information locally and on time.
</P>
<P>
All listed companies, stock trade administrators and
policy-makers are in urgent need of a fair, well-developed stock
trading information system, Deng said.
</P>
<P>
At the conference, the Chinese net expert put forward his own
creation, dubbed the "6A Comprehensive Stock Service Platform."
The six A's refer to "any time, any place, any body, any client,
any information and any service," he said.
</P>
<P>
His plan calls for the connecting of the existing national
stock trading networks as well as the Internet, and it will be
under the control of an authoritative board to unify the
management, collect data, balance the information flow, and
process the data that have entered the web.
</P>
<P>
The system will set up trunk lines hooked up to a number of
stations in large cities like Beijing and Shanghai, with every
station managing part of the network.
</P>
<P>
Existing telecommunicational networks and the public network
facilities will be used, while families will be the main clients.
</P>
<P>
As the proposed project is a huge one, experts have to plan,
design and set rules for the system in advance, and emphasis
should be put on studies over some key technology concerned, so as
to set up the network in the shortest possible time, Deng
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
