<HEADLINE> HK Chief Executive Starts Visit to U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Chief Executive of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region Tung Chee Hwa departed for
Washington this morning for the first visit to the United States
since he assumed office.
</P>
<P>
He was accompanied by Secretary for Trade and Industry Denise
Yue, his Private Secretary Joshua Law and Press Secretary Au
King-chi.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Tung is expected to meet U.S. President Bill
Clinton, as well as other government leaders, congressmen and
senators.
</P>
<P>
Tung Chee Hwa and his entourage will return to Hong Kong during
the weekend.  
