<DOCNO> XIE19970908.0248 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Media Active on Voicing People's Wishes (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"If the value of an investigative program is only measured by
mudslinging, it's popularity won't last," said Fang Hongjin, a
journalist working for CCTV's Focus Report.
</P>
<P>
In-depth reports have also caught the enthusiastic attention of
the higher echelon of state leaders, and have become a magnifying
glass through which officials at all levels can check their work.
</P>
<P>
Focus Report once reported an incident in Huaiyang County in
the central province of Henan, which said that due to poor
management of the county's grain mill, a total of 880,000 kg
of state grain reserve was damaged by mice and bugs.
</P>
<P>
A Focus Report journalist demanded an explanation from county
Party secretary Li Zhengting, and was told: "Isn't just some one
million kg of grain? So what?"
</P>
<P>
Senior Chinese officials read the report, and the Party
secretary was suspended from his post three days later.
</P>
<P>
As one provincial Party secretary said: "No government can be
free of problems in the workplace. Once a problem arises, don't
try to conceal it -- reveal and solve it."
</P>
<P>
He said that should Focus Report ever uncover any problems in
his province, he would discuss the allegations with local
officials.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970908.0249 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Village Electrification in Jiangsu Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The last group of 930,000
rural families have bade farewell to the days of no electricity,
with the 360,000 villages in east China's Jiangsu Province having
access to electrification.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government introduced a rural electrification
program to help poverty-stricken villagers in remote and
economically backward area achieve overall economic development.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu launched its "Bright Project" in 1995 and since
allocated some 700 million yuan for building and improving
power transmission and transformation facilities.
</P>
<P>
Rural areas currently account for some 56 percent of the
province's power consumption, and the electrification program has
led to the establishment of a large number of township and
village industrial enterprises. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970908.0250 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Monthly Interbank Lending Plummets in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Transactions at the
Shanghai-based interbank money market plummeted in August,
according to the lastest statistics.
</P>
<P>
Interbank borrowing and lending dived 57.5 percent from July to
17.7 billion yuan for the 21 business days of last month. The
daily transaction volume plummeted 55.5 percent to 844 million
yuan.
</P>
<P>
Official figures show that borrowings and lendings with a
maturity of 60 days accounted for 27.1 percent of the monthly
total in August, with overnight trading and that of seven days
each making up more than 24 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970908.0251 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hingis Crushes Williams to Win U.S. Open Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Top-seed Martina Hingis of
Switzerland Sunday beat American rising star Venus Williams 2-0 to
win the women's singles title at the U.S. Open.
</P>
<P>
The world number one Hingis extended her extraordinary season
record to 63-2 with a 6-0, 6-4 demolition of the unseeded Williams
in the youngest Grand Slam final.
</P>
<P>
The 16-year-old Hingis, displaying an outstanding array of
shots, thoroughly outclassed the 17-year-old Williams. Hingis
swept through the first set in just 22 minutes.
</P>
<P>
The Swiss Girl pounded the ball confidently from both sides,
controlling virtually every point against Williams, who made 38
unforced errors.
</P>
<P>
Though Williams managed to hold in the opening game of the
second set after fighting off two break points, Hingis broke
through again on her next service game for a 2-1 lead.
</P>
<P>
Williams then appeared ready to make a match of it when she
broke Hingis to even the match at 4-4, but Hingis wasted little
time exerting her superiority. The Swiss broke right back for a
5-4 lead and won the match on her first match point with a
forehand volley down the line.
</P>
<P>
Hingis, who reached all four Grand Slam finals, became the
sixth women's player, and the youngest, to win three or more major
titles in a single season.
</P>
<P>
She claimed the Australian Open and Wimbledon prior to the U.S.
Open. The only miss for the Swiss was at the French Open, where
she came back from a six-week layoff following a horse riding
accident to reach the final before losing to Croatian Iva Majoli.
</P>
<P>
Hingis earned 650,000 U.S. dollars for the victory and
Williams, who was the first unseeded player ever to reach the
women's singles final of the U.S. Open, collected 350,000
dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970908.0252 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rafter Beats Rusedski to Win U.S. Open Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Patrick Rafter of Australia
defeated unseeded Greg Rusedski of Britain 3-2 in the final to
win the title of the 10.12 million dollars U.S. Open tennis
championships in New York Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Claiming his first major title this year with a 6-3, 6-2, 4-6,
7-5 victory, Rafter became the first Australian in 24 years to
win the U.S. Open. He also ended his futility in championship
matches this year, having reached the finals five times without a
triumph.
</P>
<P>
The 13th seeded Rafter dominated play over the first two sets
with his attacking style. He broke to go up 4-2 in the first set
and then broke early in the second set as well to close out the
first two sets in one hour.
</P>
<P>
The victory moves 24-year-old Rafter to a career-high No. 3
world ranking behind Pete Sampras and Michael Chang. He won the
highest 650,000 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Rusedski, who was born in Canada and moved to Britain two
years ago, was the first British player since Fred Perry in 1936
to reach the U.S. Open final.
</P>
<P>
In an earlier match, top-seeded Martina Hingis of Switzerland
beat American Venus Williams 2-0 to claim the title of the
women's singles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
