<HEADLINE> Former Zairean President Mobutu Dies in Morocco </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RABAT, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Former Zairean President Mobutu
Sese Seko died late Sunday in the Moroccan capital of Rabat, the
official Moroccan news agency MAP reported.
</P>
<P>
Mobutu, 66, died in the Mohammed V military hospital here at
9:30 p.m. (2130 GMT), the agency said. He was suffering from
prostate cancer,
</P>
<P>
He arrived in Morocco on May 23 after the forces led by Laurent
Kabila put an end to his rule of more than 30 years. 
</P>
