<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Germany Qualifies for Under-17 Quarter-finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Germany booked a quarter-final
seat at the Under-17 World Soccer Championship after beating
Thailand on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Thailand and Costa Rica were ousted after losing two matches
apiece in their group matches.
</P>
<P>
On the fourth day of the championship, four games were played
in Cairo and the Mediterranean city of Port Said.
</P>
<P>
Germany defeated Thailand 3-0 to top Group A where Egypt and
Chile were the other teams.
</P>
<P>
In another Group A match on Sunday, Egypt tied with Chile 1-1
after conceding a 1-0 halftime lead.
</P>
<P>
This result landed Egypt in a precarious situation, with a
ticket to the last eight depending on either its win over the
powerful German team or Chile's loss to the disheartened Thailand.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the day, defending champion Ghana scored a
convincing 5-1 victory over Bahrain at Port Said.
</P>
<P>
Ghanian players were in control from the very beginning,
scoring twice in the seventh and ninth minute.
</P>
<P>
The Ghanian squad continued its attacks in the second half and
scored a third goal in the 17th minute.
</P>
<P>
Bahrain got one goal back at the 26th minute before Ghana
pulled away with two more goals.
</P>
<P>
Costa Rica was edged out of the championship after losing to
Argentina 1-0 in a Group D match in Port Said stadium. The lone
goal came at the 23rd minute.
</P>
<P>
With Ghana and Egypt each getting a red card on Sunday, four
red cards have been issued in the event.
</P>
<P>
Sixteen teams from five continents are competing in the
championship which opened here Thursday night and will run until
September 21. It is the first time that Egypt hosts a FIFA event.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
