<HEADLINE> U.S. Defeats Costa Rica in World Cup Soccer Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The United States beat
Costa Rica 1-0 Sunday in the qualitying tournament to move a step
closer to next year's World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
The goal was scored in the 78th minute by midfielder Tab Ramos
in his first World Cup qualifying match in 8 months. The victory
gave the American team three points in the CONCACAF qualifying
group.
</P>
<P>
The win moved the United States into second place with nine
points behind Mexico which has 11 in the six-team group for North
and Central America and the Caribbean region. Costa Rica is tied
for third on eight points with Jamaica which beat Canada 1-0 in
Kingston Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The top three teams will qualify for the World Cup finals in
France.
</P>
<P>
The Americans have four more matches to play -- at home to
Jamaica next month and to El Salvador and away to meet Mexico and
Canada. 
</P>
</TEXT>
