<HEADLINE> Dutch Spikers Lead Group Preliminaries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Olympic champions and hosts
the Netherlands simply proved to be too much for Ukraine on Sunday
when they wrapped a group B preliminary match within 30 minutes at
the European men's volleyball championship.
</P>
<P>
The Dutch side won the match 15-6, 15-10 and 15-1 at
Eindhoven. They now lead the six-team round-robin group
tournament with two straight wins without conceding a single set.
</P>
<P>
In other group B matches, France blanked Finland in straight
sets with scores at 15-5, 15-13, 15-7.
</P>
<P>
In group A actions at Bois-le-Duc, Slovakia scored a second win
by defeating Russia three sets to two while Germany, which went
down to the Slovaks on Saturday, managed a 3-1 win over Greece.
</P>
<P>
Following are team standings after Sunday's matches (tabulated
played, won, lost, sets for/against and points):
</P>
<P>
