<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Welcomes Albright Visit to Middle East </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Luxembourg Foreign
Minister and acting President of the Council of the European
Union, Jacques F. Poos, today expressed his support for U.S.
Secretary of State Madeleine Albright's decision to tour the
Middle East.
</P>
<P>
"I am convinced that your initiative will contribute greatly to
reactivating the search for peace in the region" at this critical
moment of the peace process, Poos said in a letter addressed to
Mrs Albright.
</P>
<P>
Albright is scheduled to go to the Middle East this week on her
first visit to the region since becoming secretary of state.
</P>
<P>
He added, "As far as the European Union is concerned, you will
not be alone in this challenging task."
</P>
<P>
Mr. Poos said that the EU was "particularly concerned to ensure
Israeli commitment to the next phase of redeployment, which is an
essential pre-requisite of the Interim Agreement."
</P>
<P>
He also said that the EU regarded "full and sustained
Palestinian cooperation" in the field of security as essential to
continued progress in the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
"In short, we regard it as essential that any restarting of the
Final Status negotiations should be accompanied by parallel
implementation of the Interim Agreement in all its aspects,
including the Hebron protocol," he emphasized in the letter.
</P>
<P>
Mr. Poos expressed the hope that both sides should avoid
unilateral acts which he believed would have a negative impact on
attempts to restart negotiations.
</P>
<P>
As a first step towards such a resuming of the peace process,
Mr. Poos said that it would be very useful if the parties
concerned could agree on a code of conduct, taking the above
points into account.
</P>
<P>
The EU has proposed the creation of a Permanent Security
Committee enabling both parties to effect joint crisis management
and possibly including U.S. and EU participation in addition to
the parties concerned.
</P>
<P>
On the short term, Mr. Poos regards "urgent action on lifting
the obstacles facing the Palestinian economy" as indispensable.
</P>
<P>
Mr. Poos expressed his satisfaction that Mrs Albright would
include Syria in her tour, saying, "The principle Land for Peace
should also apply to the Syrian and Lebanese tracks."
</P>
<P>
He therefore added that it would be very useful if Albright
would visit Lebanon as well.
</P>
<P>
Mr. Poos concluded by emphasizing that the EU would continue to
lend all its support to the region and insisted on the great
importance the EU attaches to Mrs Albright's tour in the Middle
East.  
</P>
</TEXT>
